WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.284
Bienvenue dans le tutoriel final !

00:00:03.284 --> 00:00:05.950
Faisons en sorte que vous ne manquiez

00:00:05.950 --> 00:00:07.472
plus jamais d'espace disque.

00:00:07.472 --> 00:00:10.138
Nous allons agrandir un repository complet en

00:00:10.138 --> 00:00:10.518
ligne,

00:00:10.518 --> 00:00:12.422
restituer l'espace libéré au pool,

00:00:12.422 --> 00:00:15.087
puis apprendre à la machine à faire

00:00:15.087 --> 00:00:16.229
les deux automatiquement.

00:00:17.009 --> 00:00:18.415
Voici le modèle.

00:00:18.415 --> 00:00:21.228
Chaque repository est un fichier dans

00:00:21.228 --> 00:00:23.102
un pool datastore partagé.

00:00:23.102 --> 00:00:25.915
Les repositories peuvent grandir en ligne

00:00:25.915 --> 00:00:28.727
pendant que les containers continuent de

00:00:28.727 --> 00:00:29.196
tourner.

00:00:29.196 --> 00:00:32.008
Mais supprimer des données dans un

00:00:32.008 --> 00:00:34.821
repo ne libère rien en soi.

00:00:34.821 --> 00:00:37.633
C'est le Trim qui restitue les

00:00:37.633 --> 00:00:39.039
blocs au pool.

00:00:39.039 --> 00:00:41.851
Et une policy automatise les deux.

00:00:45.131 --> 00:00:47.893
Fill the repository most of the way and

00:00:47.893 --> 00:00:48.238
check:

00:00:48.238 --> 00:00:49.964
the filesystem is getting tight.

00:00:55.905 --> 00:00:56.644
Presque plein.

00:00:56.644 --> 00:00:58.491
Il est temps de s'agrandir.

00:01:01.781 --> 00:01:03.168
Grow it online.

00:01:03.168 --> 00:01:05.942
The encrypted container and the filesystem

00:01:05.942 --> 00:01:08.717
expand while the containers keep running

00:01:08.717 --> 00:01:10.104
— zero downtime,

00:01:10.104 --> 00:01:11.028
zero unmount.

00:01:14.028 --> 00:01:15.374
Quatre gigaoctets maintenant.

00:01:15.374 --> 00:01:16.719
Rien n'a redémarré.

00:01:19.984 --> 00:01:21.404
Verify from inside:

00:01:21.404 --> 00:01:22.351
same volume,

00:01:22.351 --> 00:01:23.772
double the room.

00:01:27.914 --> 00:01:29.873
L'application n'a rien remarqué.

00:01:33.151 --> 00:01:34.734
Now the other direction.

00:01:34.734 --> 00:01:37.504
Delete the big file — but watch:

00:01:37.504 --> 00:01:40.274
the pool does not get the space

00:01:40.274 --> 00:01:41.065
back yet.

00:01:41.065 --> 00:01:43.835
Deleted blocks stay reserved inside the image.

00:01:45.585 --> 00:01:47.479
Libéré dans le repo,

00:01:47.479 --> 00:01:49.373
toujours détenu par l'image.

00:01:52.685 --> 00:01:55.267
Trim hands those blocks back to the datastore

00:01:55.267 --> 00:01:55.589
pool,

00:01:55.589 --> 00:01:55.912
online.

00:01:55.912 --> 00:01:58.171
This is the step most setups forget.

00:02:01.570 --> 00:02:02.033
Récupéré.

00:02:02.033 --> 00:02:04.809
Le pool peut respirer à nouveau.

00:02:08.085 --> 00:02:10.373
Now stop doing this by hand.

00:02:10.373 --> 00:02:13.043
The policy enables automatic growth up to

00:02:13.043 --> 00:02:14.569
a ceiling you choose,

00:02:14.569 --> 00:02:15.713
plus scheduled trims.

00:02:21.902 --> 00:02:22.984
Politique enregistrée.

00:02:22.984 --> 00:02:25.689
La machine prend le relais.

00:02:28.969 --> 00:02:30.217
Read it back:

00:02:30.217 --> 00:02:31.049
auto-grow on,

00:02:31.049 --> 00:02:32.713
ceiling at eight gigabytes,

00:02:32.713 --> 00:02:34.376
trim on a schedule.

00:02:38.106 --> 00:02:39.976
Configuré une fois,

00:02:39.976 --> 00:02:42.468
oublié en toute sécurité.

00:02:45.767 --> 00:02:48.383
And the view that ties it together:

00:02:48.383 --> 00:02:50.625
storage health shows every repo's usage,

00:02:50.625 --> 00:02:51.372
the pool,

00:02:51.372 --> 00:02:53.988
and how much copy-on-write sharing is saving

00:02:53.988 --> 00:02:54.361
you.

00:02:54.361 --> 00:02:55.868
Une vue :

00:02:55.868 --> 00:02:56.370
utilisation,

00:02:56.370 --> 00:02:58.880
économies et marge de croissance.

00:02:59.738 --> 00:03:02.333
Et voilà qui conclut la série !

00:03:02.333 --> 00:03:03.075
Dix-huit tutoriels,

00:03:03.075 --> 00:03:05.670
de l'installation au stockage en pilote automatique.

00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:07.894
Vos serveurs vous appartiennent à nouveau.

00:03:07.894 --> 00:03:09.377
Merci d'avoir regardé !
